This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with training deep learning models in the presence of label noise. It also involves the use of self-supervision, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper uses computer vision datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as these fields also involve the use of deep learning models and could potentially benefit from the proposed approach.
